text.section:
A "Nonquota type 2" or "NQ2" retail drink license may be issued to:
A hotel that:
Contains at least fifty (50) sleeping units;
Contains dining facilities for at least fifty (50) persons; and
Receives from its total food and beverage sales at least fifty percent (50%) of its gross receipts from the sale of food;
A restaurant with a minimum seating for fifty (50) consumers at tables;
An airport; or
A riverboat.
